episodes.title: Abuse of Trust (part five of five)
episodes.description: Documentary about Catholic Clerical Child Abuse in Ireland. This documentary focuses on the Dublin Diocese and has interviews from survivors who describe their horrendous experiences of sexual abuse as children, Andrew Madden and Marie Collins. This also interviews the Archbishop of Dublin, Diarmuid Martin. Links to official church web sites and summary of the commission to enquire into child abuse can be found on my channel.

episodes.title: Christine Buckley Survivor of abuse part two of two
episodes.description: A survivor of Irish clerical child abuse tells her shocking, heart-breaking story. An Irish hero, courageous and strong, Christine Buckley was one of the first victims to break her story and is an active campaigner for justice. Christine attended Goldenbridge institution and is now director of the Aislinn education and support centre at Jervis House in Dublin.

episodes.title: Ireland's Greatest Tragedy  child abuse
episodes.description:
Dedicated to the victims of abuse. So justice can finally be achieved for those who survived, and those who did not.
This video follows the publication of the report by the commision to inquire into child abuse which was published on the 20th May, 2009. The full version and the summary can be viewed here: http://www.childabusecommission.ie/
The report details the devestating extent of the child abuse within church and state run institutions throught the 20th Century in Ireland.
No other church scandal, or abuse case has ever been so severe and widespread and longlasting in  history. This will go down as one of humanity's greatest human tragedies..
